title: Wilderness' Munroe is NAHL Star of the Week
text:
Wilderness' Munroe is NAHL Star of the Week 
By Zach Schneider Wilderness' Munroe is NAHL Star of the Week September 30, 2015 Updated Sep 30, 2015 at 12:06 PM CDT 
Cloquet, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Minnesota Wilderness goaltender Chase Munroe has been named the North American Hockey League (NAHL) Midwest Division star of the week, it was announced on Wednesday morning. 
Munroe went (2-2-0) this past week at the NAHL Showcase, posting a 1.09 goals against average and a .948 save percentage.
